docs.abstract: Lawmakers and others criticized the social network after a New York Times report revealed Facebook gave its partners extensive access to user data.
docs.snippet: Lawmakers and others criticized the social network after a New York Times report revealed Facebook gave its partners extensive access to user data.
docs.lead_paragraph: Facebook and some of the other largest technology firms in the world faced sharp criticism on Wednesday for failing to disclose the extent of the social network’s data-sharing deals, many of which went back to the company’s early years.

headline.main: Facebook Rebuked for Failing to Disclose Data-Sharing Deals

docs.abstract: The follow-up to an Emmy-winning first season looks fantastic and hasn’t lost a beat, but its core story repeats itself.

docs.lead_paragraph: The high-class problem for a series that had an impressive first season is how to keep that momentum into the second. This is one problem that Amazon’s “The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel” — the first streaming series to win the best comedy Emmy — does not have.

docs.abstract: There are nations and industries in sound economic shape that are ignored by investors because they are not all about tech. Maybe that is about to change.
docs.snippet: There are nations and industries in sound economic shape that are ignored by investors because they are not all about tech. Maybe that is about to change.
docs.lead_paragraph: After a decade of extraordinary gains, the American stock market has come unhinged in recent weeks, with the technology sector leading the rapid decline. American tech giants are down on average 25 percent from recent peaks, and it appears the big global bubble of the 2010s is bursting. The question on everyone’s mind is what comes next.

headline.main: When the Bubble Bursts, Consider the Anti-Bubble
